## 🇬🇧 English

### 🎉 What's New in v7.0

**v7.0** is a complete rewrite from v5.x, focusing on three goals: cross-platform support, PDF/Print export, and a clean code + security audit pass before release.

---

### ✨ New Features

#### 📄 PDF Export & Print
- **💾 Save PDF** and **🖨️ Print** buttons appear after every scan
- PDF Page 1: Health Score, verdict, alerts, full SMART attributes table
- PDF Page 2: Complete raw JSON output from smartctl
- Automatic Thai font detection (THSarabunNew → Tahoma → Arial → Segoe UI)
- Print-friendly light theme — white/light-gray backgrounds, clear grid lines
- Native OS save dialog

#### 🎯 Health Score Bar
- Visual progress bar below the score number
- Color tracks the score: 🟢 Green (≥85) / 🟡 Amber (≥60) / 🔴 Red (<60)

#### ⚠️ Alert Panel
- Text now wraps correctly — no more truncated messages
- Error (❌🔥) and warning (⚠️) items styled distinctly
- Scrollable when many alerts are present

#### 🍎 macOS Support
- Apple Silicon (M1/M2/M3) and Intel Mac
- Privilege escalation via `osascript` — shows Touch ID / password dialog (no terminal needed)
- Automatic smartctl discovery for both Intel (`/usr/local/bin`) and Apple Silicon (`/opt/homebrew/bin`) Homebrew paths
- `build_mac.sh` produces a signed `.app` bundle and `.dmg` installer

---

### 🔧 Improvements

| Area | Details |
|---|---|
| Full Rewrite | Reduced from 1,424 → 1,226 lines |
| State Management | Consolidated `last_rows`, `last_summary`, etc. into a single `state` dict |
| Error Handling | Every subprocess has timeout + full exception handling |
| Flet Compatibility | Auto-detects flet < 0.80 and ≥ 0.80 API differences |
| PDF Thai Font | Correct font registration (regular + bold separate + registerFontFamily) |
| Dead Code Removed | Removed unused `_pad_all`, `get_resource_path`, `body_style` |

---

### 🔒 Security Audit — All Clear

- ✅ `shell=False` on every subprocess call
- ✅ User input is never concatenated into shell commands
- ✅ PowerShell injection prevented: `disk_idx` validated as `int` in range `0–99`
- ✅ smartctl invoked with read-only flags only (`--scan`, `-a`)
- ✅ No network access
- ✅ No registry access
- ✅ Temp files always cleaned up in `finally` blocks
- ✅ No debug output left in production code

---

### 📋 Requirements

```
Python       >= 3.9
flet         >= 0.9.0
reportlab    >= 3.6        (required for PDF export)
smartmontools              (external binary — see install below)
```

### 📥 Installation

```bash
pip install flet reportlab
```

**Windows** — place `smartctl.exe` in the same folder as the script  
**macOS** — `brew install smartmontools`  
**Linux** — `sudo apt install smartmontools`

---

### 📦 Release Assets

| File | Description |
|---|---|
| `blackcat_SMART_DISK.py` | Main source code |
| `build.bat` | Windows build script → `.exe` |
| `build_mac.sh` | macOS build script → `.app` + `.dmg` |
| `README.md` | Bilingual TH/EN documentation |

> **`smartctl.exe` is not bundled** — download from [smartmontools.org](https://www.smartmontools.org/wiki/Download)

---

### 🐛 Known Limitations

- macOS `.app` requires smartmontools installed on the target machine (not bundled in this release)
- PDF export requires `pip install reportlab` separately
- Linux has not been tested as extensively as Windows

---

